chunk_content: OVC Preventive participants Denominator: N/A Indicator changes None (MER v2.6.1 to v2.7): Reporting level: Facility & Community Reporting Semi-Annually frequency: How to use: One of PEPFAR’s mandates is to care for “children who have lost a parent to HIV/AIDS, who are otherwise directly affected by the disease, or who live in areas of high HIV prevalence and may be vulnerable to the disease or its socioeconomic effects” (PEPFAR authorization). To meet this mandate, PEPFAR’s Orphans and Vulnerable Children (OVC) programming serves the dual purposes of mitigating the impact of HIV/AIDS on children and adolescents and their families, as well as preventing HIV/AIDS- related morbidity and mortality. COP Guidance details an approach to risk and resilience for the OVC portfolio that responds to the current stage of the HIV/AIDS pandemic and the child’s needs.
